      "span_text": "Furthermore, tenofovir is effective against lamivudine-resistant HBV  and appears to reduce the rate of lamivudine resistance when the combination is used.  Adefovir at the approved dose for HBV (10 mg) has negligible activity against HIV. To date, no resistance to HIV has been detected up to 144 weeks in small studies."
